3 Part 2: Model relationship between DBH and height

Assume that this set of 31 is a representative sample of ALL Eastern Hemlocks on Smith College campus, and thus any inferences/results based on this sample can generalize to all Eastern Hemlocks on Smith College campus.

  1. Fit a model, any model, for \(y\) = height of the tree using diameter at breast height.
  2. A forest ecologist asks How would you quantify the relationship between tree height and diameter at breast height? Respond to them.
  3. Visualize this model. There are many ways to do this, but here is one way:
library(tidyverse)
library(broom)

# Fit model
mpg_model <- lm(mpg ~ hp, data = mtcars)

# Look at fitted values and residuals using broom::augment()
augment(mpg_model) %>% head()
.rownames mpg hp .fitted .resid .std.resid .hat .sigma .cooksd

# Visualize observed data with black points and fitted values with red line
ggplot() +
  geom_point(data = mtcars, aes(x = hp, y = mpg)) +
  geom_line(data = augment(mpg_model), aes(x = hp, y = .fitted), col = "red")
